A Chrome extension designed for developers working with GoJS, providing comprehensive tools for diagram model analysis and debugging. This extension enhances the development workflow by offering detailed insights into diagram components and their underlying data structures.

Key Features

- Diagram Inspection: 

       Visual highlighting of diagram objects, nodes, and links

       Precise object selection and property examination

- Structural Exploration:

       Tree-view interface for diagram model navigation

       Comprehensive access to nodeDataArray, linkDataArray, and modelData

       Hierarchical object property traversal

       Class inheritance inspection

- Developer Console Utilities:

       Global diagram references ($diagram)

       Runtime diagram object storage

       Enhanced debugging capabilities

- Documentation Integration:

       Direct links to GoJS documentation

       Context-specific property references

       Reduced context switching for developers

Technical Benefits

This extension provides developers with a structured approach to understanding and manipulating GoJS diagram models. It addresses common challenges in visualization development by offering granular inspection and debugging tools that streamline the development process.

The extension supports efficient diagram model analysis, helping developers quickly identify, understand, and modify complex visualization structures.
